		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2668381)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2668381">
																		Random Article Review #4, 10 October 2016
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kalinin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2203795); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2203795&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610225860" alt="Kalinin" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2203795)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/kalinin" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2203795); return false;" >Kalinin</a></span> <span class="odate time_1476138400 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">10 Oct 2016 22:26</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2668381">
									

<p>I have to imagine that 682 was still somewhat novel as a subject back in 2010, though I found the huge amount of stories about it to be pretty played-out not long after I joined in 2012. &quot;682-fic&quot; is so prevalent around here that you could really consider it a separate genre at this point, but it's not one that I've ever really found very compelling. That's probably the biggest portion of my downvote.</p>
<p>I would say that this falls into the trap that a lot of sci-fi does with aliens that are way closer to humans than they should be, but I really don't know a whole lot about the race that's visiting the solar system here, and that's my chief complaint regarding the narrative itself. The viewpoint is that of an alien species, and while it's 682 that's the star of the show, I would have liked a little bit more of that alien intellect to leak into the story. It <em>kind of</em> does that through the reaction of the guests to what I think most people would consider to be a horrifying monster, but not enough to really differentiate these creatures or make them feel like characters in the story.</p>

							</div>

								
					
